txt.en: 'Long did the Witch-king of Angmar mock me...'
'Even in failure and defeat, he would not release me.'
'Where you beheld redemption, I saw only desperation...'
'But now he is vanquished, and I have slipped from his grasp!'
'A final, futile reach for relevance in the Dark Lord's designs...'
'I spoke true when I said that the man I had been was gone...'
'Even as she drew her last breath, she knew...'
'...but no longer am I a servant, and no longer am I a Steward!'
'There remained nothing that could undo her deeds.'
'I am the King returned!'
'From the depths of Mordor, I summon thee!'
'To the Shadow... to the Flame...'
'I bind thee!'
'Rise, servant of the Dark Lord!'
'RISE!'
'Bathe in my sorcery and smother these lands!'
'Steel yourself or see your hope stripped away!'
'Away with you, curs!'
'Bathe in my power!'
'You are undone!'
'The fires of Mordor come for you!'
'Your allies will abandon you...'
'Your past haunts you...'
'Evils sleep within the hearts of Men... and I wake them!'
'Give in to your fear!'
'Surrender, beast!'
'...only to fail.'
'We must subdue him once more!'
'...even as the Darkness breaks.'
'Alas for Golodir...'
'Protect me, you beasts!'
'...or face your undoing!'
'The poor fool lingers in the North, dwelling on his loss...'
'He must not... break free!'
'...knowing nothing of how deep his failure has been!'
'Death to those who oppose the returned King!'
'My strength is fading...!'
'At last he understands the lessons of his time in my keeping, but far too late.'
'More to claim for the King's keeping...'
'I... cannot hold...'
'He has only himself and his blind quest for vengeance to blame for the West's undoing!'
'Do not let them escape!'
'Your fate... cannot be avoided...'
'I have failed you, my King...'
'Do you hear it, little ones? The screams of the innocent beyond the walls?
'Without your Master, what power have you?'
'I shall delight in delivering them to their deaths!'
'You shall know fear yet - wraiths of Minas Morgul!'
'You cannot stand against me...'
'Let none return to that accursed vale!'
'I am but a hammer before a field of nails!'
'They are upon us too soon!'
'Go! Defend the binders until it submits to our wills!'
'I shall hold them back for as long as I can...'
'Hssssss!'
'Vengeance for the Black Serpent!'
'You bend to my will...'
'You waste your effort, fools!'
'Reeve Herubrand and Herefara were caught in the Enemy's advance...'
'Whether my doom comes at your hand or another, you shall not find victory this day, Orc!'
'The shadows of Angmar are cast upon you!'
'I must protect the Reeve and his son if I may!'
'Leave my son in the peace of death!'
'Face me, Orc! You shall not touch them again!'
'You have my thanks... Nothmar...'
'Farewell, my friend. You and your son shall rest easy - I swear it!'
'When I am gone, bear us away from this place...'
'Leave me, friends! I shall see their bodies from the field.'
'I go... to join my son...'
'Go! The day is not yet done!'
'Twice you cast me into the Void, but never again!'
'While pitiful Golodir lives, I cannot be ended.'
'The shards of Dúnachar bind our wills as one.'
'My Master is slain and now I command a force beyond imagining!'
'Mordor, Khand, Harad, Rhûn, and Angmar all rise against you!'
'Let us see who is the stronger now!'
Throne of the Dread Terror
Haradrim reinforcements strike from the south!
'...and you serve the Master.'
'The thrones of Minas Morgul and Minas Tirith are mine!'
'The battle rages on, but you hide in your memories!'
'A pity you cannot hide from the Morgul-host!'
'Pathetic!'
'What hope have you with a mind so frail?'
'I am finished humouring you, little ones!'
'This is your final lesson!'
'Surrender now or be slain to the last!'
'No! That is not his fate!'
'Back to the shadow...'
'The Dread Terror comes for you...'
'Enough!'
'You think that I would see you slain?'
'No... no.... such a fate is too kind for you.'
'There is far more suffering for you to endure...'
'You shall witness the fall of the West from Minas Morgul...'
'...and the deaths of your pitiful allies!'
'I go to reclaim my throne. Lock them away under the watch of my Knights!'
'Feel the might of Sauron!'
'I draw you forth...'
'Here our fates were bound, [placeholder]...'
'Dúnachar was again thrust into me...'
'...and all went light.'
'But again I was pulled back from the Void...'
'...and I swore to conceal myself until my Master's hour was at hand.'
'And so it has come! Even the skies strike at you now!'
'You have come so far...'
'There is no death for us...'
'Conquer your fears...'
'Worry not, friends. I shall free you!'
'There! Now, let us join the battle!'
'Here it began...'
'On each new day, Golodir searched for a glimpse of hope in the palantír.'
'Yet, there was none to be found.'
'They're sending more against us! Form up, maggots!'
Endless waves of Orcs and Uruks rush onto the road ahead!
'Your doom is cast!'
'Snap out of it, you cowards!'
'...and you serve your purpose.'
